The paper deals with the problem of joint inband backhauling and interference mitigation in 5G heterogeneous networks, which is a topic related to network communication and information theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the use of random matrix theory and stochastic optimization, which are topics related to information theory and systems and control theory, respectively. Hence, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also likely categories. The paper also mentions the use of massive MIMO and small cells, which are topics related to multimedia and mobile computing. Therefore, cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category. Finally, the paper deals with network utility maximization, which is a topic related to computer networks. Hence, cs.COM (Computer Networks and Communications) is also a possible category.
